
## The Forbidden Way

The Forbidden Way (German: Der verbotene Weg) is a 1920 German silent film directed by Henrik Galeen and starring Lupu Pick, John Gottowt and Edith Posca.

# Cast 

Lupu Pick as Amtsmann
John Gottowt as Lucas
Edith Posca as Susanne
Lina Lossen as Frau Amtmann
Wilhelm Diegelmann as Amtsvorsteher
Eugen Rex as Amtsdiener
Sophie Pagay

# References 

